					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Found the problem, and the crosstalk pattern is now going at a 45Â° angle:<br /><br /><img src="http://i.imgur.com/X26NwqI.png" alt="Image" /><br /><br />The problem code was in the decoder:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">for (int v = 0; v &lt; 262; v++) {<br />&nbsp; for (int h = 0; h &lt; 341 * 2; h++) {<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; auto center = (v * 8 * 341) + ((h / 2) * 8);<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; auto x1 = center - 4;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; auto x2 = center + 4;<br /></div><br /><br />The formula for the <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">center</tt> variable should instead be:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; &nbsp; auto center = (v * 8 * 341) + ((h * 8) / 2);<br /></div><br /><br />Otherwise you fall victim to integer math truncating the remainder.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

